{"id": "EUVD-2025-10331", "enisaUuid": "2b1b0277-023c-3d30-95f6-469e987e6dd9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nARM: dts: bcm2711: Fix xHCI power-domain\n\nDuring s2idle tests on the Raspberry CM4 the VPU firmware always crashes\non xHCI power-domain resume:\n\nroot@raspberrypi:/sys/power# echo freeze > state\n[   70.724347] xhci_suspend finished\n[   70.727730] xhci_plat_suspend finished\n[   70.755624] bcm2835-power bcm2835-power: Power grafx off\n[   70.761127]  USB: Set power to 0\n\n[   74.653040]  USB: Failed to set power to 1 (-110)\n\nThis seems to be caused because of the mixed usage of\nraspberrypi-power and bcm2835-power at the same time. So avoid\nthe usage of the VPU firmware power-domain driver, which\nprevents the VPU crash.", "datePublished": "2025-04-08T08:18:01", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T18:14:52", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-22011", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/393947e06867923d4c2be380d46efd03407a8ce2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b8a47aa0b3df701d0fc41b3caf78d00571776be0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f44fa354a0715577ca32b085f6f60bcf32c748dd"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-22011", "GHSA-rcwx-9pp2-6rpj"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "067ba5fd-a5a4-3346-aa96-83bea8766a18", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.8"}, {"id": "321d72c8-240b-339d-b0ac-b188fd8f1eea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14"}, {"id": "5bab8f39-6668-3be9-a99f-3a80a35f8ef0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "522c35e08b53f157ad3e51848caa861b258001e4 <b8a47aa0b3df701d0fc41b3caf78d00571776be0"}, {"id": "a3c9adc2-0429-3214-8eda-537b06ba3ac5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.21"}, {"id": "b723631c-70db-35a6-ba5e-40c5e4132f47", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_v